        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Assistance for Cultivation of Medicinal/ Aromatic Crops&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to encourage the cultivation of medicinal and aromatic plants to promote alternative agriculture and improve farmers&amp;#39; income.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - Financial assistance up to 75% of the cost or ₹11,250/- per hectare, whichever is lower.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme provides financial assistance up to 75% of the cost or ₹11,250/- per hectare (whichever is lower) to farmers in Gujarat cultivating medicinal or aromatic crops on land between 0.20 and 4 hectares.\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
